Heat your #grill{} to the highest setting. Line a flat #baking tray{} with #foil{} and drizzle with oil. Halve the @lime{1}. Pop the @miso paste{15%g}, @honey{15%g}, a drizzle of oil and a squeeze of lime juice in a large #bowl{}. Mix well, add the @cod fillets{2} and coat well. Pop the cod onto the lined baking tray and drizzle any remaining marinade over the top of the fish. Place under the grill until just cooked and the top is turning golden brown, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle. Wash your hands after handling raw fish.

Quarter the @shiitake mushrooms{50}. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} or #wok{} on high heat. Once hot, add the @aromatic vegetable mix{1} and the mushrooms, stir fry for ~{2%minutes} then add the @soy sauce{25%ml} and cook until the vegetables are just tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, cook the @coconut chilli lemongrass steamed basmati rice{1} according to pack instructions. Cut the remaining lime into wedges. Divide the rice between plates, top with the vegetables and any pan juices then the cod and scatter over the @salted peanuts{25%g}. Serve with the lime wedges. Enjoy!